  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "PatchCore [68], SPADE [63] and PaDim [73] conduct the ablation study on 16 normal training samples.",
    "None of them, however, are specialized in few-shot anomaly detection.",
    "Hence, it is necessary to develop new algorithms that concentrate on native few-shot anomaly detection tasks.Recently, researchers extended the zero-shot anomaly detection (ZSAD) setting beyond the FSAD setting.",
    "The goal of ZSAD is to leverage the generalization power of large models to solve anomaly detection problems without any training, thus completely eliminating the cost of data collection and annotation.",
    "MAEDAY [142] uses a pretrained masked autoencoder (MAE) [143] to tackle the problem."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "PatchCore [68], SPADE [63] and PaDim [73] conduct the ablation study on 16 normal training samples.",
    "MAEDAY [142] uses a pretrained masked autoencoder (MAE) [143] to tackle the problem."
